01:13:42.053 --> 01:13:43.220
NANCY KANWISHER: The false--

01:13:43.220 --> 01:13:45.710
there isn't an obvious
discrimination that you can do.

01:13:45.710 --> 01:13:48.800
See, the nice thing about the
moral reasoning task is it's

01:13:48.800 --> 01:13:53.000
got these two outcomes-- these
two conditions, accidental harm

01:13:53.000 --> 01:13:54.120
and intentional harm.

01:13:54.120 --> 01:13:56.780
So that gives us a way to go
in and do the pattern analysis

01:13:56.780 --> 01:13:57.715
questionnaire.

01:13:57.715 --> 01:13:59.090
So with false
beliefs, you'd have

01:13:59.090 --> 01:14:03.380
to think of some other
dimension to look at.

01:14:03.380 --> 01:14:05.060
And the experiments
are not set up

01:14:05.060 --> 01:14:09.410
that way with stimuli that are
